This bash script polls the rss feed for a few nasa websites which post images often. As soon as an image is uploaded by NASA, it is downloaded and set as a wallpaper.

Setup:
1. Download the files sdesk.sh and url.txt into a folder which is in PATH (e.g. ~/bin)
2. Run chmod u+x sdesk.sh to grant executable permissions.
3. Run ./sdesk.sh -s to setup the installation
4. Run nohup ./sdesk.sh & to run the script.
5. Add the script to startup applications with commandline: nohup sdesk.sh & 




